Magic in the Current Age
Magic today is a pale echo of the Golden Age. Only about one in a thousand individuals is born with any magical aptitude. Cases of two aptitudes in one person are exceptionally rare and highly prized. Without proper training, even talented individuals can rarely cast more than the simplest effects. Modern spellcasting relies almost exclusively on chanted incantations; the lost arts of chantless casting, multi-casting, and instantaneous spells are known only from ancient texts that few can read.
The most common aptitudes belong to the four primary elemental schools: Fire (Pyromancy: Flames, explosions, lava, heat manipulation), Water (Hydromancy: Waves, waters, steam), Wind (Aeromancy: Gusts, flight, sound, vacuum) and Earth (Geomancy: Stone, metal, sand, crystal shaping). Less common are Lightning (Electromancy: Thunder, bolt, plasma, speed enhancement), Light (Photomancy: Holy radiance, light orb, flash, illusions of purity), and Nature ((Biomancy / Wood: Plants, animals, poison, growth, fungal networks) (especially among elves and fae). Holy (Healing, blessings, exorcism, smiting evil, divine protection, purification) and Dark (Umbramancy: Shadows, darkness, fear, absorption) magic appear rarely. Spirit magic (Communicating with and commanding ancestral spirits, elementals, kami) is occasionally seen in elves and faeries. Necromancy (Undead raising, soul manipulation, life drain, resurrection) manifests unpredictably across all races but is outlawed in most civilized kingdoms under penalty of death, so parents rarely bring such children forward for testing.
Virtually all advanced schools of magic were lost after the Shattering and have not reappeared in living casters. These “Lost Magics” include:

Abjuration (shields, anti-magic fields, wards)
Conjuration (summoning, familiars)
Transmutation (material conversion and manipulation)
Illusion (Phantoms, invisibility, mind tricks, false realities)
Polymorph (shapeshifting into beasts, animal, dragons, Wyverns)
Divination (Future sight, scrying, truth detection)
Curse magic (Debuffs, misfortune, corruption)
Soul Magic (Soul binding, soul transfer, memory reading/wiping, reincarnation techniques)
Teleportation / Gate Magic (Instant movement, portal creation, pocket dimensions, warp)
Void Magic (Reality tearing, summoning from other worlds, phasing)
Time Magic (Chronomancy: Acceleration, slowing, limited time loops, aging/rejuvenation)
Blood Magic (Blood control, contracts, life-force fuel, forbidden rituals)
Rune / Inscription Magic (Permanent enchantments on objects, tattoos that grant powers)
Enchantment Magic (temporary enchantments on objects)
Telepathy / Psionics (Mind reading, thought projection, psychic shields)
Dream Magic (Dreamwalker: Entering dreams, dream manipulation, nightmare inducement)
Emotion Magic (Amplifying or suppressing feelings, love/hatred spells)
Demon / Infernal Magic (Pacts with demons, hellfire, corruption)
Dragon Magic (Ancient draconic spells, breath weapon mimicry, hoard-based power)
Godsbane Magic (Directly counters or kills gods)
Chaos Magic (Random powerful effects, hard to control)
Death Magic (True Necromancy variant: Killing concepts, entropy acceleration)
Aetherforge Magic (was mostly dwarven: Combines Aetherite metals with spells for dimensional weapons)
Gravity / Stellar Magic (Black holes, meteors, orbital strikes, weight manipulation, floating islands)
Music / Bardic Magic (Sound-based buffs, debuffs, reality-altering songs)
Cooking / Household Magic (buff-granting meals and enchantments, cleaning)
Luck / Fortune Magic (Manipulating probability) (different from pure luck, luck magic affects specific probability events)
Fate Weaving (Reading and altering destiny threads, prophecy enforcement, curse of inevitability)
Taming Magic (Taming, evolving, or fusing with monsters)
Weather / Climate Magic (Controlling seasons, creating localized disasters)
Corruption / Blight Magic (Turning land into dungeons, mutating creatures, spreading miasma)

Unique Magic provided by Gods:
Appraisal: Analyzing items, people, and hidden stats. Complex magical skill. It classifies the analized data in a presentable form creating a list of magic skill, normal skill, special skill and their level of 
Gluttony: Absorbs a targets skills, magical aptitudes, magical abilities, special skills, monster skills, unique abilities
GetCreative/Edit/Bestow: Divine ability to create, edit and bestow any skill and any magic
Language Comprehension: Read, write, talk, understand any language ever.

Traces of these lost arts still exist in ancient ruins, enchanted relics, lingering barriers, and half-understood scrolls. Their echoes shape the world even if the ability to wield them has faded.
Magic Use: Current users need chants to manifest magical power (disadvantage: the user needs time to chant the specific spell). Those chants give structure to the users imagination and intent to create specific results. For instance, a fireball is difficult to conceptualize, so the chant gives that structure a form an intent. Chants are not necessarily needed, but no one can cast without them anymore. Users usually can only cast one spell at a time, but reports/legent exist of two casting, how they cast 2 spells is a mistery since a person can only chant one spell at a time. Speculation is that they use silent casting. Chantless, multi-cast, fast casting was normal practice in the magic golden age woith some mages being able to cast dozen at the same time.

Magical users per race: Humans 1 in 1000, Elves 1 in 300, Dwarves 1 in 4000, Beastkin 1 in 1500, Demons/Devil: Unknown
Some minor races like the fae, gnome have much more common use of magic
